manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Why can't I watch Netflix/Hulu movies on this projector? We can use a streaming device such as a Roku or Amazon Fire Stick, or use HDMI cable to connect computer to play video. ( Like most projectors on the market, copyrighted content from Hulu, Netflix etc. CANNOT be mirrored or screencast. ) Why do I have no sound when watching Video? This projector does not support Dolby sound. Please turn off Dolby sound on the devices or apps. ( Settings → Display & Sounds → Audio → Dolby Digital Output →Turning OFF Dolby Digital ) Can I zoom the image size without changing the projector distance? (Refer to the QA video for more details) Yes, the projector can zoom the original image from 100% to 50% without changing the projection distance. (“M” button → picture → Reduce Image Size → OK button → “>” button) Is the projector compatible with my Google phone, Xbox gamepad? How to make the projector better heat dissipation? 1. Due to copyright issues, projectors are not compatible with products such as Google-owned phones or Xbox gamepad. 2. Please take out the dust-proof net from the bottom of the projector regularly and wipe off the dust to get better cooling effect. How to get a sharp image？ 1. Place the projector on a level table and perpendicular to the wall. 2. Open the menu interface of the projector, first adjust the keystone button to make the image a regular rectangle, and then adjust the focus button to make the picture clear.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 21, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Beautiful sound and decent display
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. Sound and video work great! I bought this device back in 2022 and it still holds up strong. Make sure you buy a good stand to get the best quality. The projector works excellent in tandem with my play station and my switch. It connects to Bluetooth pretty easily (although I don’t use it often). It’s a handy projector perfect for the college student who doesn’t have the space to carry around a large tv during frequent moves.Mine did manage to develop a blue overlay as I used it more but it became more noticeable when the screen is pitch black. Beyond that it didn’t bother the display as much.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars It depends on your expectations!
reviews.reviewText: I bit on this item based on the price and reviews, but I think a savvy buyer should have proper expectations set. If this is your first purchase of a digital projector, then you have zero expectations, and then this product is probably fine. If however, you’ve used products from known brands (the types sold in technology oriented box stores) then this thing is just a toy. I purchased it based on price and reviews to replace a ten year old projector from a known global brand. I wanted the built in WiFi and Bluetooth but the image quality and brightness pale in comparison to my current, and well outdated tech, despite the description on Amazon. To suggest this thing dishes out 1080 is a stretch and 4K is laughable (although, I’m not thinking that’s possible from any projector to be fair). It’s fine for the kids to watch cartoons, but if you want a real cinema experience, look elsewhere. Again, to be fair, I may have had unrealistic expectations for $130 bucks. My current projector was probably $500+ on sale.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 13, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Good! Edited more comments
reviews.reviewText: Got it out the nicely secured package and was satisfied by the looks. Had accessories and it worked great. 2 problems tho. 1 was the wifi. I just don't understand the mirror feature and don't got time to waste on it. 2 was the sound. I fixed this after awhile of brainstorming lol dummy moment. Uh i went to settings for sound and turned off each stereo input. It worked after i turned off dolby. Other than that just get the cheaper one without the wifi if you looking for no nonsense. Just added this a week after I bought it. This projector got a star back because I noticed during the day the screen looks just as good as night. Last projector I had it absolutely had to be dark. Or it would be a glare but this one no prob can watch in any lighting
